## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1f4ee-104">Il metodo deve essere statico e pubblico.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1f4ee-104">The method must be static and public.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1f4ee-105">Deve restituire una raccolta di tutte le istanze della classe WMI.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1f4ee-105">It must return a collection of all instances of the WMI class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1f4ee-106">La raccolta può essere di qualsiasi tipo convertibile in <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1f4ee-106">The collection can be of any type convertible to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerable>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="1f4ee-107">Nell'esempio seguente viene illustrato come utilizzare l'attributo Enumerator per contrassegnare un metodo che consente di enumerare le istanze di una classe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1f4ee-107">The following example shows how to use the Enumerator attribute to mark a method that is used to enumerate instances of a class.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="1f4ee-108">In questo caso, il metodo Enumerate utilizza il <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> classe per recuperare tutti i processi in esecuzione nel computer.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1f4ee-108">In this case, the Enumerate method uses the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> class to retrieve all of the processes running on the computer.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
[ManagementEnumerator]  
public static IEnumerable Enumerate()  
{  
   Process[] rgProcesses = Process.GetProcesses();  
   for (int i = 0; i < rgProcesses.Length; i++)  
   {  
      yield return new ProcessProvider(rgProcesses[i]);  
   }  
}  
```
